This is the raw 'bit mask' of RBs allocated (used) (for slot 0 - first stream of data if in mimo conditions). The count of '1' bits in this is the 'number of RBs used'.

This is the raw 'bit mask' of RBs allocated (used) (for slot 1 - second stream of data if in mimo conditions). The count of '1' bits in this is the 'number of RBs used'. (this allocation is normally always the same as slot 0 alloc above.
This is the actual meaningful 'Number of RBs used'. The 'Last' postfix means the last value in the normally 200ms reporting duration.

This is the actual meaningful 'Number of RBs used'. The 'Avg' postfix means that this is the average of the 200 samples of this value in the normally 200ms reporting duration. (So this is a 'floating point' value - not decimal).
